text.tspan: Color blocking individual sections isolates information
in a way that allows the mind to navigate and absorb it
with increased ease and organizational emphasis. This
can be used to isolate expandable sections of
information such as in the display/hide function of a
disclosure triangle, and may most effectively reduce
complication when dealing with large amounts of
information.
This approach is most appropriate when the informa
tion
can logically and effectively be grouped into sim
lar cat
egories, and when not doing so results in confu
sion due to visual clutter.
Not color blocking sections of information keeps the
canvas fragmentation to a minimum.
This approach is most appropriate when the
information cannot logically or effectively be grouped
into similar
categories and needs more verbose
descriptors to effec
tively communicate the various
types of settings options available, or when color
blocking would be unnecessary due to existing clarity
in the information structure.
